Step 1: Check if Notepad++ is available
notepad++

If it says "command not found", you need to add Notepad++ to your system's PATH.

How to Add to PATH (Windows):
1.Go to Control Panel > System > Advanced System Settings
2.Click Environment Variables
3.Under User Variables, edit the Path and add the Notepad++ installation path (e.g., C:\Program Files\Notepad++)

Now restart Git Bash and check again:
notepad++

Step 2: Set Notepad++ as Git editor
git config --global core.editor "'C:/Program Files/Notepad++/notepad++.exe' -multiInst -notabbar -nosession -noPlugin"

To verify:
git config --global --edit
